WEBVTT

04:20.067 --> 04:21.192
That's it.

04:24.655 --> 04:26.824
- How you doing'?
- What's up?

04:27.908 --> 04:29.034
All right.

04:29.910 --> 04:31.120
Pick it up.

04:32.538 --> 04:33.622
Look out.

04:34.540 --> 04:35.666
Coming through.

04:35.749 --> 04:38.127
You have to tell me where to turn.

04:56.562 --> 04:57.688
I knew it.

04:58.272 --> 04:59.731
She's not here.

05:00.315 --> 05:01.900
Frank! Sidney!

05:01.984 --> 05:03.610
I'll try the basement.

05:03.819 --> 05:05.028
Don't panic.

05:05.320 --> 05:07.281
She's around here somewhere.

05:08.365 --> 05:10.075
Faye!

05:10.826 --> 05:12.244
Come on out!

05:23.172 --> 05:24.256
You, you!

05:25.883 --> 05:28.844
Did you ever hear of private property?

05:29.720 --> 05:31.889
Just coming for a hamburger, pop.

05:32.139 --> 05:35.267
You got a lot of nerve!
Get your food somewhere else!

05:35.768 --> 05:36.935
Who's that?

05:37.311 --> 05:40.314
Take off that hat so I can get a look at you.

05:40.773 --> 05:42.566
Here she is. Faye!

05:42.649 --> 05:44.985
For the love of Mike, where you been?

05:45.736 --> 05:48.197
You scared the living daylights out of me!

05:48.280 --> 05:49.615
I did the marketing.

05:49.698 --> 05:52.117
Somebody's got to do the marketing.

05:57.539 --> 05:59.833
What are you looking at?

06:00.501 --> 06:02.544
Nothing, pop. Nothing.

06:03.629 --> 06:05.088
Was that Bobby?

06:05.422 --> 06:07.049
I think it was Bobby.

06:07.132 --> 06:09.968
No, dear, it wasn't Bobby.

06:10.385 --> 06:12.221
It was just a man.

06:12.638 --> 06:15.557
Now, how about I fix your breakfast?

06:16.975 --> 06:19.019
I don't smell no bacon on.

06:19.686 --> 06:21.105
Is this Sunday?

06:22.064 --> 06:24.149
Monday and Tuesday don't smell at all...

06:24.233 --> 06:26.610
...because Cream of Wheat is instant.

06:27.027 --> 06:28.362
And it ain't Thursday.

06:28.445 --> 06:33.158
I can smell Thursday all the way back
to Wednesday when people put the garbage out.

06:34.201 --> 06:36.787
If it's Sunday, we got to walk in the park.

06:36.870 --> 06:37.871
Sure.

06:38.997 --> 06:39.998
Sid.

06:40.165 --> 06:43.043
Why don't you kids
come for a walk with us?

06:43.127 --> 06:46.046
Sure, Faye. That sounds great.

07:09.153 --> 07:10.654
Get off.

07:10.821 --> 07:12.656
Hola, Mami.

07:13.449 --> 07:14.450
Look.

07:14.950 --> 07:16.368
Smell like money?

07:16.452 --> 07:17.870
Because it is.

07:29.298 --> 07:30.799
He didn't write.

07:30.883 --> 07:32.968
Take it from me. I know about this stuff.

07:33.051 --> 07:34.636
He ain't coming back.

07:34.887 --> 07:37.806
This is the letter
you've been waiting for.

07:39.475 --> 07:42.019
Come on, you're a very rich lady.

07:42.644 --> 07:44.772
Take it! What's wrong with you?

07:44.855 --> 07:46.899
Fresh cash money.

07:47.775 --> 07:49.902
She doesn't believe me.

07:49.985 --> 07:51.904
You could move to Brooklyn.

07:58.452 --> 08:01.246
Here. Buy yourself a new saint.

08:01.747 --> 08:03.540
You can afford it now.

08:11.215 --> 08:12.466
Room service!

08:15.594 --> 08:17.513
It's moving day, Picasso!

08:25.938 --> 08:26.855
Bee.

08:27.231 --> 08:29.274
Don't you even want to count it?

08:29.358 --> 08:31.819
They're paying you to move out.

08:39.743 --> 08:42.162
Hey, doll. He's not home?

08:42.287 --> 08:44.289
How about you move in with me?

08:44.414 --> 08:47.292
This place here, it's falling apart.

08:47.501 --> 08:49.128
No! Don't! Get--

08:58.470 --> 08:59.763
Bee!

09:02.015 --> 09:03.016
Bee?

09:03.851 --> 09:04.893
It's us.

09:07.438 --> 09:09.064
The "knock-knock" boys.

09:11.775 --> 09:13.819
Let's punch it out again, champ.

09:13.902 --> 09:15.028
Round two!

09:24.538 --> 09:26.081
How's the face, man?

09:26.415 --> 09:28.375
You ready for a rematch?

09:29.668 --> 09:31.795
Yesterday, we got rough.

09:32.379 --> 09:34.089
Today, we got money.

09:34.923 --> 09:36.884
Tomorrow, you ain't gone...

09:46.018 --> 09:48.562
There, now you got less to move.

09:49.563 --> 09:51.648
And here's your prize money.

10:04.036 --> 10:05.579
Where are the boys?

10:05.746 --> 10:07.706
I don't hear them playing.

10:08.916 --> 10:09.917
Bobby!

10:10.209 --> 10:11.543
Donald!

10:11.752 --> 10:15.005
Donald's all grown up, Faye.

10:16.548 --> 10:18.884
He has two kids of his own now.

10:19.301 --> 10:21.345
I'm a grandmother, remember?

10:21.428 --> 10:22.179
Yeah.

10:22.262 --> 10:24.973
Now, sit down and finish your coffee.

10:26.225 --> 10:27.810
But where's my Bobby?

10:28.936 --> 10:31.396
Get out of my place, you punks!

10:31.480 --> 10:34.149
Mr. Riley, it's your lucky day!

10:34.233 --> 10:37.861
You, too, pops. Social Security, that's me.

10:38.362 --> 10:41.782
Now, you move out, you go to Miami...

10:41.865 --> 10:45.327
...you sit in the sun, listen to Bing Crosby...

10:45.410 --> 10:47.412
...play checkers, bingo.

10:47.496 --> 10:50.249
- We don't want any trouble, Carlos.
- Hallelujah!

10:50.332 --> 10:53.168
- Don't touch it!
- Too late, man. She already took it.

10:53.252 --> 10:56.630
- You're an angel, Bobby.
- I'm calling the cops!

10:56.713 --> 11:00.092
- Faye, time for your medicine.
- Let Mama give you a pucker.

11:00.175 --> 11:03.428
Never knew you had a mother.
[Buenos dias, seirora!

11:03.512 --> 11:04.972
Shut up, Benny.

11:05.556 --> 11:10.269
You got the idea, right?
You take the money and move out, okay?

11:10.352 --> 11:11.895
Get out of my way!

11:12.396 --> 11:14.731
Let the boy help you.

11:14.815 --> 11:16.984
You never give him a chance. Bobby!

11:17.067 --> 11:18.318
Stop calling me that!

11:18.402 --> 11:20.571
Get them out of here. And you.

11:20.696 --> 11:23.866
Stay away from my wife and this building.

11:23.991 --> 11:27.161
You tell Lacey his money stinks!
You understand?

11:27.536 --> 11:29.872
You kill my head, man.

11:30.456 --> 11:32.458
Money's not a good reason to move?

11:32.541 --> 11:34.460
Okay, here's a good reason.

11:40.466 --> 11:42.801
That's right, abuela. Break it up.

11:43.844 --> 11:45.679
- Come on, Faye.
- Throw him out!

11:45.763 --> 11:47.347
We'll talk about it later.

11:47.431 --> 11:48.348
Frank!

11:49.308 --> 11:50.350
You punks!

11:50.434 --> 11:52.811
Take your hands off of me!

12:03.405 --> 12:05.824
Chill out, pop. You're going to go bald!

12:05.908 --> 12:07.826
You dirty bastards!

12:08.035 --> 12:10.120
Take it easy, pops.

12:10.204 --> 12:11.538
No!

12:31.558 --> 12:33.352
...at fine stores everywhere.

12:33.435 --> 12:35.145
<i>Batteries not included.</i>

12:42.945 --> 12:44.071
Lacey!

12:47.491 --> 12:48.742
No, you don't!

12:48.909 --> 12:51.120
Lacey, you son of a bitch!

12:51.203 --> 12:53.622
You're not getting away with it!

12:56.166 --> 12:59.086
Lacey, open up and face me like a man!

12:59.586 --> 13:01.505
You're not throwing me out!

13:03.924 --> 13:06.468
You really think
that he'd come down here?

13:06.552 --> 13:09.847
Take the money, Mr. Riley. It's our last offer.

13:22.067 --> 13:25.529
This is my place! It's all I got.
I grew up here, for God's sake!

13:25.612 --> 13:27.489
What do you want us to do'?

13:27.573 --> 13:30.284
Arrest them.
Send them up the river for life.

13:30.576 --> 13:34.037
- I'm not scared. I'll testify.
- You know what'll happen.

13:34.121 --> 13:36.915
They'll have 18 witnesses saying
they were somewhere else.

13:36.999 --> 13:39.376
When they get out,
they'll come after you again.

13:39.460 --> 13:42.379
Then patrol the neighborhood,
for crying out loud!

13:44.548 --> 13:46.008
What neighborhood?

13:52.806 --> 13:54.516
What the hell happened?

13:54.600 --> 13:55.726
Mind your own business.

13:55.809 --> 13:59.146
Wait a minute. I live here. Upstairs.

13:59.980 --> 14:02.608
Yeah. I've seen you.
You're in Moskowitz' old place.

14:02.691 --> 14:05.569
Mr. Baylor, do you honestly think...

14:05.652 --> 14:09.156
...I could recommend this building
for historic preservation?

14:09.490 --> 14:12.618
Mrs. Thompson,
it was in much better shape this morning.

14:12.701 --> 14:14.036
I doubt that.

14:14.328 --> 14:16.079
Yeah. Look at the moldings.

14:16.163 --> 14:17.956
Look, look at the cornice.

14:18.832 --> 14:20.292
That's terra cotta.

14:21.168 --> 14:23.086
You don't like ornament. All right.

14:23.170 --> 14:25.422
Step back here and look at those proportions.

14:25.506 --> 14:30.219
- It's got style. It's got dignity.
- There's nothing to preserve.

14:30.302 --> 14:32.805
This one's still here. It can be saved, restored.

14:32.888 --> 14:34.973
We do have a minimum standard...

14:35.057 --> 14:37.768
...that the structure is intact and livable.

14:37.935 --> 14:39.311
You don't even have that.

14:39.394 --> 14:40.854
People live here.

14:42.314 --> 14:43.565
Not for long.

15:16.181 --> 15:18.892
Look, if you're so nervous, I'll fix the door.

15:18.976 --> 15:20.936
It's not the door, Mason.

15:21.019 --> 15:22.104
It's you.

15:22.187 --> 15:24.815
You and your fascination with this place.

15:25.065 --> 15:26.650
What? I like it here.

15:26.817 --> 15:29.653
Of course you do. It's old and depressing.

15:29.820 --> 15:31.280
It's reality!

15:32.573 --> 15:34.116
This is the '80s, Mason.

15:34.199 --> 15:36.577
Nobody likes reality anymore.

15:37.661 --> 15:40.873
Why don't you admit it? It's time to quit.

15:41.206 --> 15:44.168
Thank you very much. How do you know that?

15:44.251 --> 15:45.669
You said so yourself!

15:45.752 --> 15:48.213
You said that you were going nowhere.

15:48.505 --> 15:53.844
You could do analytic deconstruction,
Neo-Geo, hard-edge.

15:53.927 --> 15:57.723
But, no, you've got to be
the Andrew Wyeth of the East Village.

15:59.308 --> 16:03.061
Why don't you go back to your father
and sell vans or rec-Vs...

16:03.145 --> 16:05.272
...or whatever they're called.
-RVs.

16:05.355 --> 16:08.275
But for God's sake, get out of here.

16:09.276 --> 16:13.906
To think that I've been telling my
friends that it's so cool living with an artist!

16:14.531 --> 16:17.451
You never once asked to paint me nude!

16:28.629 --> 16:31.089
Stop right here, man!

16:31.215 --> 16:32.716
All right!

16:36.637 --> 16:37.763
Sorry.

16:45.646 --> 16:47.773
It's okay, Frank. She's here.

16:48.148 --> 16:49.775
She's been helping.

16:50.400 --> 16:52.945
- Give it to me.
- I called Donald.

16:53.445 --> 16:55.030
He made the arrangements.

16:55.114 --> 16:57.574
For what? A funeral?

16:59.284 --> 17:00.911
We're going to Jersey.

17:01.787 --> 17:04.289
It's a home for senior citizens.

17:06.415 --> 17:08.001
You took their money.

17:09.711 --> 17:12.214
You took that bastard's money.

17:12.464 --> 17:15.217
There's cold cereal in here...

17:15.300 --> 17:17.094
...and a Libby's canned fruit...

17:17.176 --> 17:19.221
...but she won't eat the cherries.

17:19.304 --> 17:22.266
And beans. She just loves beans.

17:22.348 --> 17:24.560
Frank, where's our bags?

17:24.810 --> 17:26.645
It's the Love Boat to Cuba.

17:26.728 --> 17:31.233
Shuffleboard and pineapples filled with rum.

17:31.316 --> 17:32.651
You know what they do'?

17:32.734 --> 17:35.487
They put paper umbrellas sticking out the top...

17:35.571 --> 17:38.991
...so when it rains,
it don't thin out the liquor.

17:39.992 --> 17:44.913
And here's her Enderol, four times a day...

17:45.372 --> 17:49.918
...after meals and at bedtime,
and her HydroDIURIL twice a day...

17:50.002 --> 17:51.753
...and don't forget.

17:51.837 --> 17:53.297
I got it.

17:54.089 --> 17:55.841
I won't forget. I'm okay.

17:56.467 --> 17:59.720
Frank, we're tired.

18:00.471 --> 18:03.682
It's not a home anymore.

18:04.558 --> 18:06.560
Say goodbye for us, will you?

18:06.769 --> 18:09.980
Hell, she won't even know you're gone.

18:43.514 --> 18:44.973
Come on out, Faye.

18:45.057 --> 18:46.016
Let's do this.

18:46.100 --> 18:47.392
Where's Muriel?

18:47.851 --> 18:50.187
It smells like cherry cordial, this stuff.

18:50.270 --> 18:51.271
Muriel!

18:52.064 --> 18:55.275
I'm Muriel now. I'm coming in, Faye.

18:55.359 --> 18:57.319
Hold it, I ain't dressed.

18:57.402 --> 18:59.363
Get Frank. Frank!

18:59.822 --> 19:01.115
Yeah'?

19:01.990 --> 19:03.325
Who's that?

19:04.493 --> 19:05.953
It's Frank.

19:06.036 --> 19:07.913
I'm Frank now.

19:08.539 --> 19:09.623
Okay.

19:20.050 --> 19:21.969
Put on the red record.

19:22.302 --> 19:24.012
We haven't got a red record.

19:24.096 --> 19:27.641
Muriel has a red record. Makes the pills go down.

19:27.724 --> 19:28.642
Sure.

19:33.605 --> 19:37.693
- Say "ah."
-No. Muriel and I say "frog."

19:38.068 --> 19:41.822
- Frog.
