38:56.769 --> 38:59.062
Robert. Mr. B.

38:59.146 --> 39:00.606
Shut up!

39:01.023 --> 39:03.901
I saw downstairs.
Who's been cleaning up after me?

39:05.486 --> 39:06.653
Who?

39:09.865 --> 39:12.159
Whoever threw that is ruined, man.

39:12.242 --> 39:13.827
Hospitalized.

39:44.024 --> 39:46.568
What the hell is this'?

40:03.085 --> 40:06.380
Whoever's in there, you got big trouble, man.

40:20.936 --> 40:21.937
Carlos.

40:22.938 --> 40:25.566
Actually, I wouldn't do that if I were you.

41:07.024 --> 41:10.235
Carlos, where are you going, man?
Let's talk this over!

41:10.402 --> 41:12.070
Don't forget to write!

41:19.161 --> 41:23.040
Okay, easy now, little guy. That's right.

41:23.207 --> 41:26.460
I just want to check for that label that says,
"Made in the USA."

41:26.543 --> 41:29.838
No, don't. You'll queer our luck.

41:29.922 --> 41:32.883
That little guy is the golden goose.

41:51.276 --> 41:53.362
It serves you right.

41:56.573 --> 41:59.159
We apologize. He didn't mean to pry.

41:59.243 --> 42:01.120
He was just being scientific.

42:01.203 --> 42:03.747
"GE." This says "GE."

42:04.039 --> 42:07.209
This is, was, my coffeepot.

42:07.751 --> 42:09.628
Looks like it's been percolated.

42:09.711 --> 42:11.338
Who are they, Frank'?

42:11.505 --> 42:14.466
What is so special about our roof?

42:16.051 --> 42:17.761
Maybe it was me.

42:20.013 --> 42:22.099
What do you mean you?

42:23.809 --> 42:25.227
Me and Faye...

42:26.520 --> 42:27.980
...we needed help.

42:30.607 --> 42:34.653
You think that they're here because of you?

42:36.029 --> 42:40.826
The quickest way to end a miracle
is to ask it why it is...

42:42.327 --> 42:44.955
...or what it wants.

42:53.589 --> 42:55.174
What is your name, dear'?

42:55.257 --> 42:58.218
- Marisa.
-Marisa. Boy, my memory.

42:58.302 --> 43:02.181
It's like the Navy.
Coming and going, coming and going.

43:02.973 --> 43:05.601
Here's Bobby's Iittlejammies.

43:05.684 --> 43:08.270
I bet there's even a few diapers in here.

43:08.353 --> 43:10.773
How old is your son, Mrs. Riley?

43:11.690 --> 43:12.858
Bobby?

43:14.359 --> 43:15.903
Let me see.

43:16.695 --> 43:18.655
He just had a birthday.

43:19.490 --> 43:21.825
I've got to think.

43:23.118 --> 43:25.120
He's got his father's ears.

43:26.705 --> 43:30.459
He and Frank don't get along so good.

43:31.418 --> 43:34.671
Frank's got a terrible temper, you know.

43:38.258 --> 43:40.511
You're going to love being a mother.

43:41.428 --> 43:43.347
Faye, come here, quick!

44:35.941 --> 44:38.569
- What are they doing'?
- Can't you tell?

44:52.499 --> 44:54.418
She's going to get hungry.

44:55.502 --> 44:57.171
Take it away!

45:07.014 --> 45:08.307
It's too short!

45:08.849 --> 45:10.893
- Any more?
- That's it.

45:11.310 --> 45:13.645
Come on, Frank. They're starving.

45:16.815 --> 45:19.318
Well, what do you know'? Thanks, Harry.

45:20.652 --> 45:22.446
I saw you fight.

45:22.821 --> 45:25.365
Harry Noble, the human locomotive.

45:26.867 --> 45:29.787
Come on, Harry, say something. Talk to me.

45:32.164 --> 45:34.249
Come on, Frank. Get on with it.

45:35.125 --> 45:36.668
A tremendous right.

45:37.127 --> 45:38.295
Tremendous.

45:39.088 --> 45:40.547
Never says a word.

45:40.631 --> 45:44.343
Just watches TV. Loves the commercials.

45:46.804 --> 45:48.472
It's all we got.

45:50.849 --> 45:52.684
Come on. Take it.

45:53.352 --> 45:56.730
It's okay. We're neighbors.

46:00.067 --> 46:02.319
- Doesn't trust us.
-Yeah.

46:26.051 --> 46:29.471
Harry Noble. I used to bet on him.

46:29.763 --> 46:32.891
He had a hell of a right. You should've seen him.

46:54.580 --> 46:57.750
Look out. Flying pot.

46:58.584 --> 47:00.878
Ghost in the garbage!

47:01.170 --> 47:02.838
Shut up, Benny.

47:03.255 --> 47:07.050
Mama's whole kitchen coming to get you.

47:07.134 --> 47:09.136
I said shut up, man!

47:10.637 --> 47:12.222
Lighten up.

47:12.431 --> 47:14.933
We got plans for those people.

47:15.392 --> 47:16.852
And you know what?

47:17.770 --> 47:20.856
Those people are making plans on their own.

47:20.939 --> 47:23.025
They got something hooked up.

47:24.526 --> 47:27.738
Man, they're getting organized, and look at us.

47:29.531 --> 47:30.949
Somebody's helping them.

47:31.033 --> 47:33.702
Somebody's bringing them together.

47:33.827 --> 47:37.998
- Yo, Carlos, I see someone.
- Give me that!

47:46.298 --> 47:48.133
Wave to your mother.

48:05.067 --> 48:06.860
There you are.

48:07.986 --> 48:11.698
You're a lucky one. She's a darling girl.

48:33.804 --> 48:35.556
Are you superstitious?

48:35.764 --> 48:37.599
I'm getting there.

48:38.100 --> 48:39.226
Well...

48:41.520 --> 48:43.605
...I'm not superstitious...

48:44.773 --> 48:48.485
...but I was thinking about these things
and why they came.

48:49.570 --> 48:50.779
And...

48:53.532 --> 48:55.742
This will really sound silly, but...

48:55.826 --> 48:59.079
...it's like they were watching or listening.

49:00.164 --> 49:03.584
- You think they're here because of you.
- Yes!

49:08.881 --> 49:10.716
So when's the baby due?

49:11.175 --> 49:13.302
Two or three more months. I'm not sure.

49:13.385 --> 49:15.596
You're not sure'? What does the doctor say'?

49:15.679 --> 49:18.140
- I haven't been to the doctor.
-That's crazy.

49:18.223 --> 49:20.601
- I feel fine.
-You got to take care of yourself.

49:20.684 --> 49:24.062
My boyfriend's coming.
He's going to take care of me.

49:24.146 --> 49:26.356
- Your boyfriend.
-Hector.

49:26.523 --> 49:29.234
He's a musician, so he travels around a lot...

49:29.401 --> 49:30.986
...different places.

49:32.362 --> 49:35.282
So, what about you? No more girlfriend'?

49:35.365 --> 49:37.743
No, she got smart.

49:38.827 --> 49:41.038
Don't say that. She'll be back.

49:41.121 --> 49:43.499
- Yeah'? Why should she?
- Because.

49:44.416 --> 49:45.834
You're an artist.

49:46.877 --> 49:49.171
Oh, God, an artist.

49:50.464 --> 49:53.175
- Can I come in?
- No.

49:53.967 --> 49:57.429
- I make a very artistic cup of coffee.
- No...

49:58.097 --> 50:00.557
I want to go to bed to sleep.

50:01.683 --> 50:03.393
I have to take a nap.

50:06.146 --> 50:07.940
Did I say something wrong'?

50:09.274 --> 50:13.070
No, it was nice talking to you.
I'll see you tomorrow, okay?

50:14.154 --> 50:15.197
Okay.

50:16.406 --> 50:17.658
See you tomorrow.

50:21.203 --> 50:22.621
Mason!

50:25.082 --> 50:26.959
Maybe it was for you.

50:27.209 --> 50:28.210
What?

50:28.627 --> 50:31.296
Maybe they're here, those things...

50:31.630 --> 50:33.090
...because of you.

50:45.352 --> 50:48.730
- Give me back my camera, man.
- Go chase phenomena, man.

50:48.814 --> 50:52.109
- Bust it up, Benny!
- Want to do business? Severance pay.

50:52.317 --> 50:54.736
Want to see a strange object?

50:56.488 --> 50:57.948
There you go, fool!

51:24.183 --> 51:25.601
Frank!

51:30.481 --> 51:31.899
What's happening?

51:39.281 --> 51:42.117
- Tonight's the night.
- Already?

52:01.595 --> 52:04.556
The fuses! She blew the fuses.

52:14.525 --> 52:15.943
There it is.

52:51.145 --> 52:53.897
- How's she doing'?
-it happened.

52:55.232 --> 52:56.984
I'm a grandmother.

53:13.083 --> 53:14.668
It's twins!

53:15.210 --> 53:17.087
This calls for cigars.

53:17.963 --> 53:19.882
- You got any cigars?
- Cigars?

53:20.674 --> 53:22.092
This is history.

53:23.969 --> 53:26.680
Do you realize what's going on here?

53:27.347 --> 53:29.975
Machines that reproduce themselves.

53:31.226 --> 53:35.105
Spare parts with intelligence. Living hardware.

53:39.777 --> 53:43.781
I don't know how you got here,
or why you picked us...

53:43.864 --> 53:47.451
...but we pledge allegiance...

53:47.993 --> 53:50.913
...to honor and protect you...

53:53.040 --> 53:55.250
...in sickness and in health...

53:55.334 --> 53:57.044
...in rain and sleet...

53:57.127 --> 54:00.047
...in the best of times and the worst of times...

54:01.256 --> 54:03.383
...so help us, God.

54:03.467 --> 54:04.718
What's that?

54:33.747 --> 54:35.916
Batteries not included.

55:07.990 --> 55:10.951
"The Lord is my shepherd,
I shall not want.

55:11.743 --> 55:14.079
